```sql
-- Select objects with high probability (>0.6) of being Cepheid, Delta Scuti, or RR Lyrae
WITH selected_objects AS (
    SELECT p.oid
    FROM probability p
    WHERE p.class_name IN ('CEP', 'DSCT', 'RRL')
      AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
      AND p.classifier_version = 'hierarchical_rf_1.1.0'
      AND p.probability > 0.6
      AND p.ranking = 1 -- most probable class
    LIMIT 100
)
-- Retrieve all columns from probability and ps1_ztf for these objects
SELECT p.*, ps.*
FROM probability p
JOIN ps1_ztf ps ON p.oid = ps.oid
WHERE p.oid IN (SELECT oid FROM selected_objects)
  AND ps.sgscore1 > 0.8;
```

```sql
-- Select objects with W1-W2 color less than 1, including specified columns
SELECT 
    o.oid AS ztf_identifier,
    o.ndet AS number_of_detections,
    (f_g.magmin - f_r.magmin) AS mag_diff_g_minus_r,
    f_w1_w2.value AS w1_w2,
    f_w1_w2.version AS feature_version
FROM 
    object o
-- Join feature table for g-band (fid=1)
JOIN 
    feature f_g ON o.oid = f_g.oid AND f_g.name = 'g-W2' AND f_g.fid = 1
-- Join feature table for r-band (fid=2)
JOIN 
    feature f_r ON o.oid = f_r.oid AND f_r.name = 'g-W2' AND f_r.fid = 2
-- Join feature table for W1-W2 color
JOIN 
    feature f_w1_w2 ON o.oid = f_w1_w2.oid AND f_w1_w2.name = 'W1-W2'
WHERE 
    f_w1_w2.value < 1
-- Limit to 100 results
LIMIT 100;
```

```sql
-- Select specific columns for objects with W1-W2 color less than 1
SELECT 
    o.oid AS ztf_identifier,
    o.ndet AS number_of_detections,
    (f_g.magdif_min - f_r.magdif_min) AS mag_diff_g_r,
    f_w1_w2.value AS w1_w2,
    f_w1_w2.version AS feature_version
FROM 
    object o
JOIN 
    feature f_w1_w2 ON o.oid = f_w1_w2.oid
JOIN 
    feature f_g ON o.oid = f_g.oid AND f_g.name = 'g-r_max' -- assuming magdif_min is stored under 'g-r_max'
JOIN 
    feature f_r ON o.oid = f_r.oid AND f_r.name = 'g-r_max' -- same as above, for r-band
WHERE 
    f_w1_w2.name = 'W1-W2'
    AND f_w1_w2.value < 1
    AND f_g.name = 'g-r_max'
    AND f_r.name = 'g-r_max'
LIMIT 100;
```

```sql
-- Select objects with high probability of being YSOs and exhibiting periodicity
SELECT 
    o.oid,
    p.probability AS possibility,
    f.value AS feature_value,
    f.name AS feature_name,
    f.fid AS filter_id,
    f.version AS feature_version
FROM 
    object o
JOIN 
    probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
JOIN 
    feature f ON o.oid = f.oid
WHERE 
    p.class_name = 'YSO'
    AND p.classifier_name IN ('lc_classifier', 'lc_classifier_top', 'lc_classifier_transient', 'lc_classifier_stochastic', 'lc_classifier_periodic', 'stamp_classifier')
    AND p.probability > 0.7
    AND f.name = 'Period_band'
    AND f.value BETWEEN 3 AND 10
    AND EXISTS (
        SELECT 1
        FROM feature f2
        WHERE 
            o.oid = f2.oid
            AND f2.name = 'Amplitude'
            AND f2.value > 0.5
    )
ORDER BY 
    p.probability DESC;
```

-- Select relevant information for objects classified as SN II with specified conditions
WITH sn_ii_objects AS (
    SELECT o.oid
    FROM object o
    JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
    WHERE p.class_name = 'SNIII'
      AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
      AND p.probability > 0.6
      AND p.ranking = 1
      AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN '2019-01-01' AND '2022-12-31'
      AND o.ndet > 50
      AND EXISTS (
          SELECT 1
          FROM magstat m
          WHERE m.oid = o.oid
            AND m.fid IN (1, 2) -- g and r bands
            AND m.magmax_corr - m.magmin_corr > 0.5 -- initial rise estimate > 0.5 mag
      )
)
SELECT
    d.oid,
    d.candid,
    d.mjd,
    d.magpsf,
    d.sigmapsf,
    f.name AS band_name,
    -- Calculate initial rise rate for g and r bands
    CASE
        WHEN f.fid = 1 THEN
            -- For g band
            (MIN(d2.mjd) FILTER (WHERE d2.mjd > d.mjd) - d.mjd) AS time_to_first_detection,
            (d2.magpsf - d.magpsf) / (d2.mjd - d.mjd) AS rise_rate
        WHEN f.fid = 2 THEN
            -- For r band
            (MIN(d2.mjd) FILTER (WHERE d2.mjd > d.mjd) - d.mjd) AS time_to_first_detection,
            (d2.magpsf - d.magpsf) / (d2.mjd - d.mjd) AS rise_rate
        ELSE NULL
    END
FROM detection d
JOIN object o ON d.oid = o.oid
JOIN magstat m ON o.oid = m.oid AND m.fid = d.fid
JOIN feature f ON o.oid = f.oid AND f.fid = d.fid
LEFT JOIN detection d2 ON d.oid = d2.oid AND d2.mjd > d.mjd AND d2.fid = d.fid
WHERE
    o.oid IN (SELECT oid FROM sn_ii_objects)

```sql
-- Select relevant information for objects classified as SN II with specified conditions
WITH sn_ii_objects AS (
    SELECT o.oid
    FROM object o
    JOIN probability p ON o.oid = p.oid
    WHERE p.class_name = 'SNIII'
      AND p.classifier_name IN ('lc_classifier', 'lc_classifier_top', 'lc_classifier_transient', 'lc_classifier_stochastic', 'lc_classifier_periodic', 'stamp_classifier')
      AND p.probability > 0.6
      AND p.ranking = 1
      AND o.ndet > 50
      AND o.firstmjd BETWEEN '2019-01-01' AND '2022-12-31'
)
SELECT
    d.candid AS candidate_id,
    d.mjd AS time,
    d.magpsf AS magnitude,
    d.sigmapsf AS mag_error,
    -- Calculate initial rise estimate as the difference in magnitude over the time difference
    (d.magpsf - lag(d.magpsf) OVER (PARTITION BY d.oid ORDER BY d.mjd)) / NULLIF((d.mjd - lag(d.mjd) OVER (PARTITION BY d.oid ORDER BY d.mjd)), 1e-9) AS initial_rise_rate,
    d.fid AS band_id
FROM detection d
JOIN sn_ii_objects s ON d.oid = s.oid
WHERE d.oid IN (SELECT oid FROM sn_ii_objects)
  AND d.mjd >= (SELECT firstmjd FROM object WHERE oid = d.oid)
  AND d.mjd <= (SELECT mjdendhist FROM object WHERE oid = d.oid)
  AND d.fid IN (1, 2) -- g and r bands
ORDER BY d.oid, d.mjd;
```

```sql
-- Select specified columns for objects with given ZTF identifiers and zero dubious corrections in g band
SELECT 
    o.oid AS "ZTF identifier",
    m.ndet AS "number of detections",
    m.dmdt_first AS "initial rise estimate",
    m.dm_first AS "first difference magnitude"
FROM 
    object o
JOIN 
    magstat m ON o.oid = m.oid
WHERE 
    o.oid IN ('ZTF20adadshh', 'ZTF21aaabvit', 'ZTF21aaabvjk')
    AND m.fid = 1 -- g band
    AND m.ndubious = 0;
```

```sql
-- Select up to 50 objects with specified probability thresholds for AGN and LPV classifications
SELECT 
    o.oid AS ztf_id,
    sp.probability AS prob_stamp_agn,
    lp.probability AS prob_lc_lpv
FROM 
    object o
-- Subquery to get the highest probability of being AGN in the stamp classifier version 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        p.oid,
        p.probability
    FROM 
        probability p
    WHERE 
        p.class_name = 'AGN'
        AND p.classifier_name = 'stamp_classifier_1.0.4'
        AND p.ranking = 1
        AND p.probability > 0.6
) sp ON o.oid = sp.oid
-- Subquery to get the highest probability of being LPV in the light curve classifier
JOIN (
    SELECT 
        p.oid,
        p.probability
    FROM 
        probability p
    WHERE 
        p.class_name = 'LPV'
        AND p.classifier_name = 'lc_classifier'
        AND p.ranking = 1
        AND p.probability > 0.7
) lp ON o.oid = lp.oid
-- Limit the result to 50 objects
LIMIT 50;
```
